1. Create a VPC

- Name : Service Consumer VPC
- Range : 192.168.0.0/24

2. Create two subnet

* Choose VPC ID : Service Consumer VPC
* Choose AZ : ap-south-1

* Subner One : 
- Name : GWLBE_endpoint_Subnet
- Range : 192.168.0.0/25

* Subnet Two :
- Name : App_Subnet
- Range : 192.168.0.128/25

3. Create Route Table

[1] Create route table 
> Name : "GWLBE_endpoint_Subnet_RT"
> VPC : Select "Service Consumer VPC" > Create route table
> Associate subnet : Edit subnet association > "GWLBE_endpoint_Subnet" > Save Association

[2] Create Second Subnet
> Name : "App_Subnet_RT"
> VPC : Select "Service Consumer VPC" > Create route table
> Associate subnet : Edit subnet association > "App_Subnet" > Save Assocation

4. Create Internet Gateway

Name : IG-For-Service-Consumer
> Attach IG with VPC (Service Consumer VPC)

Now Go to Route Table

* "GWLBE_endpoint_Subnet_RT" > Edit Route > 0.0.0.0/0 | Internet Gateway - choose IGW > Save
* "App_Subnet_RT" > Edit Route > 0.0.0.0/0 | Internet Gateway - choose IGW > Save

5. Create EC2 Instances 

[1] First Instance

- Name : Web_Server_1
- Choose keypair
- Networking setting > Edit
	Select Subnet : "App_Subnet" 
	Enable : Assign Public ip
	Create Security Group : Name : 'Web-Server-SG', Type : All traffic and add Access from everwhere

- Add this user data script
	
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
systemctl enable httpd.service
systemctl start httpd.service
echo "Hello this server One" > /var/www/html/index.html

[2] Second EC2 instance

- Name : Web_Server_2
- Choose keypair
- Networking setting > Edit
	Select Subnet : "App_Subnet"
	Enable : Assign Public ip
	Select Security Group : Web-Server-SG (Preveously created)

- Add this user data script

#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
systemctl enable httpd.service
systemctl start httpd.service
echo "Hello this server Two" > /var/www/html/index.html

6. Create VPC

Name : Service Provide VPC
ipv4 CIDR :  192.168.1.0/24
Done 

7. Create Subnet

VPC ID : Service Provide VPC 	
Name : Firewall_Subnet
Choose AZ : ap-south-1
Subnet : 192.168.1.0/24 

8. Create Route Table

Name : Firewall-Subnet-RT
VPC : Service Provide VPC
Subnet Association : Add > Firewall_Subnet > Done

9. Create Internet Gateway

Name : IG-For-Service-Provider
Create Done then Next
Attach VPC : choose "Service Provide VPC"

* Now go to Route Table > Firewall-Subnet-RT > Edit Route > 0.0.0.0/0 --- Choose Internet Gateway --- igw-IG-For-Service-Provider >  Save

